        "terms": {
          "gt0001": {
            "id": "gt0001",
            "text": "Geriatric Depression Scale 15 (GDS-15)",
            "description": "The 15-item Geriatric Depression Scale (GDS-15) is a shortened version of the original GDS, designed to screen for, assess, and help diagnose depression in older adults. It may be incorporated into routine geriatric assessments, particularly in primary care, outpatient psychiatric clinics, inpatient settings, and long-term care facilities. The tool can be either self-administered or completed with the assistance of a practitioner. In addition to screening, the GDS-15 can be useful for monitoring depressive symptoms and evaluating the effectiveness of treatment over time."
          },
